WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   SINGAPORE -- Singapore's trade deficit narrowed to $679.1
million Singapore (US$362.6 million) in March from $1.83
billion Singapore in February, and was narrower than the gap
of $1.07 billion Singapore in March 1989.
   March imports rose to $9.27 billion Singapore from $8.41
billion Singapore in February, and were up from $8.49 billion
Singapore in March 1989.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Exports rose to $8.59 billion Singapore from $6.58 billion
Singapore in February and $7.42 billion in March 1989.
</TEXT>
