<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   SEATTLE -- Alaska Airlines said April traffic increased
16% to 322 million revenue passenger miles from 278.5 million
in the year-ago month. The passenger load factor, the
percentage of available seats occupied by fare-paying
passengers, declined slightly to 49.6% from 50.9%.
   For the first four months of 1990, the Alaska Air Group
Inc. unit flew 1.28 billion revenue passenger miles, up 18%
from 1.08 billion in the same period a year ago. The
passenger load factor dropped to 49.1% from 49.8%.
