   Phoenix Re 1st-Quarter Loss
</HL>
<DATE>
05/04/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   PXRE
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Phoenix Re Corp. reported a first-quarter loss
and declining revenue, due mostly to catastrophic events in
Europe.
   The loss was $1.9 million, or 48 cents a share, compared
with profit of $1.5 million, or 37 cents a share, a year
earlier. Revenue for the quarter declined 15% to $8.3 million
from $9.8 million a year ago.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The loss stemmed primarily from three European storms and
a major hailstorm in Sydney, Australia. Phoenix, which
provides reinsurance products and services internationally,
said it had set aside a $4 million loss reserve for claims
arising from these events.
