<LP>
   SYDNEY -- Australian Mutual Provident Society, the
country's largest insurance concern, said its assets under
management rose 89% to 57.6 billion Australian dollars
($43.34 billion) in 1989, from A$30.4 billion a year earlier.
   The funds don't include assets of Pearl Group PLC, a
British life-insurance concern that AMP acquired in the past
year for #1.24 billion ($2.04 billion).
</LP>
