<LP>
   OIL CITY, Pa. -- Quaker State Corp. said its Valley Camp
Coal Co. subsidiary received a five-year contract to supply
390,000 tons of coal annually to the Philip Sporn electric
generating plant at New Haven, W.Va.
   The power plant is owned by two units of American Electric
Power Co., Columbus, Ohio.
</LP>
<TEXT>
